# TypeScript strict mode
- Enable strict, noUncheckedIndexedAccess, exactOptionalPropertyTypes.
- No `any` types. Use `unknown` and narrow.
- All functions have explicit return types.

# Deterministic boundaries
- Side effects must be explicitly declared.
- Every boundary evaluation returns one of 4 states.
- Test vectors define expected outcomes upfront.

# Babble DSL
- Custom language in babble/ directory.
- Policies compile to TypeScript runtime.
- No external DSL dependencies.

# CI gates
- Publication requires all gates to pass.
- No manual overrides allowed.
- Audit log records every gate evaluation.
